FBIS4-62760 "drsov096_b_94026" FBIS-SOV-94-096 Daily Report 18 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military Issues Reportage on Pacific Fleet Ammunition Dump Explosion Reportage on Pacific Fleet Ammunition Dump Explosion Officials Quell Sabotage Motive LD1805053494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0506 GMT 18 May 94 LD1805053494 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yuriy Grachev] [Text] Vladivostok May 18 -- The Pacific Fleet ammunition storage facility exploded on May 14 because of irresponsibility and negligence in guarding the facility, the local counterintelligence service reported, denying earlier rumours about an alleged act of subversion and the arrest of a suspect whose actions were motivated by pecuniary interests, and search for an accomplice. According to Pacific Fleet counter-intelligence sources, a guard off duty found a discarded electric device, part of a rocket acceleration unit which incorporates a gunpowder charge, left unattended on the premises. He took the thing up an began to dismantle it with the help of a penknife, with another guard off duty watching him do it. The knight slipped and struck the charge which ignited on impact. The first guard hurled the burning unit aside where last year grass caught the fire at once, setting aflame a stack of jet shells. The frightened soldiers fled from the scene without doing anything to extinguish the fire or notifying the unit commander of the incident. The first explosion followed within minutes. The military prosecutor of the garrison has instituted criminal proceedings and the investigation continues.
